modules.description: Provides functions to parse and render codicon glyphs from Unicode code points, including mapping between icon names and their corresponding symbols. Works with strings, integers, and custom record types representing icon metadata. Used to dynamically generate icon displays in text-based interfaces and to convert between human-readable names and glyph representations.

Provides functions to extract a codicon's frame number, name, and SVG representation with customizable size and color. Works with a custom type representing codicons, enabling integration with virtual DOM structures. Used to render scalable icons in web interfaces with precise styling controls.
